div.p:
"Not very—but often enough. I do not believe mamma cares about it now. At first I
                  was afraid she did, and it vexed me. But this has nothing to do with my flowers;
                  why did you say, I must not sell them?"

"So I think now; but then, Charles, I loved my uncle so dearly, and he wished it;
                  and my refusal at first had made Donald so miserable—I thought it must be right to
                  do what would make them happy, even though it made me very unhappy."
